BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Breakwater Book Launch
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T190000
UID:bm-4835820260415@shop.benmcnallybooks.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://cdn1.bookmanager.com/i/7600763/Website2/
 Events/2026_Leslie_Shimotakahara.png?cb=1773167220
DESCRIPTION:[at Ben McNally Books]\nJoin us at Ben McNally Books\, in part
 nership with Cormorant Books\, to celebrate the launch of\nThe Breakwater\
 n\, by Leslie Shomotakahara.\nOrder a Copy of the book here.\nAbout the B
 ook\nOne morning in Toronto\, Cathy Matsumoto’s father\, Yasuo\, calls t
 o announce he intends to visit a dying cousin in Victoria.\nCathy’s neve
 r heard of this mysterious relative before\, but she begrudgingly agrees t
 o plan a cross-country family trip.\nIt's only in British Columbia that Ca
 thy learns this “cousin” is actually Yas’s younger brother\, Stum\, 
 who’s been languishing in psychiatric care for decades\, abandoned\, eve
 r since Yas committed him to Essondale Asylum before World War Two\, inadv
 ertently sparing Stum from the atrocities of the Japanese Canadian internm
 ent camps.\nYas tries to fend off probing questions from his daughter\, bu
 t revisiting old haunts stirs up memories of the brothers’ boyhood rival
 ry and coming-of-age near Victoria’s Chinatown\, when Yas’s steely res
 olve to hold their fractured family together clashed against Stum’s trou
 blesome turn toward a life of gambling\, crime\, and consorting with prost
 itutes.\nIn this stirring multigenerational saga\, two brothers\, both old
  men not far from death\, must at last confront long-buried family secrets
  — and their lingering effects on subsequent generations.\nAbout the Aut
 hor\nLeslie Shimotakahara is an award-winning author of three novels and a
  memoir\, as well as numerous short fiction and essays. She won the Canada
 -Japan Literary Prize (2012) and has been shortlisted for the K.M. Hunter 
 Artist Award. Her writing has appeared in the National Post\, World Litera
 ture Today\, and other anthologies and periodicals. She holds a PhD in Eng
 lish from Brown University\, and lives in Toronto with her husband.
LOCATION:Ben McNally Books
URL:https://shop.benmcnallybooks.com/events
X-SOURCE:Ben McNally Books
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:City Rising 4: The Age of Dry Water Book Launch
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260424T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260424T190000
UID:bm-4792920260424@shop.benmcnallybooks.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://cdn1.bookmanager.com/i/7600763/Website2/
 Events/2026_City_Rising.png?cb=1772825038
DESCRIPTION:[at Ben McNally Books]\nJoin us at Ben McNally Books\, in part
 nership with At Bay Books\, to celebrate the launch of\nThe Age of Dry Wat
 er\nand the completion of the\nCity Rising Tetralogy\n\, by David Rotenb
 erg.\nOrder a Copy of the book here\n.\nSee the whole series here.\nAbout 
 the Book\nBook 4 and the final climatic end in the acclaimed\nCity Rising 
 Shanghai Tetralogy\n. Two prophecies are put forward\; one proceeds\, the 
 other is fulfilled\, and a city at the Bend in the River grows.\nA sprawli
 ng historical epic spanning 200 years\, City Rising tells the story of two
  destitute Baghdadi Jews who become opium lords\, their battles against th
 e powerful British opium companies\, and the boys' eventual love of the Ci
 ty at the Bend in the River - Shanghai.
LOCATION:Ben McNally Books
URL:https://shop.benmcnallybooks.com/events
X-SOURCE:Ben McNally Books
END:VEVENT
